description: apside +‎ -al, from apsides, from Ancient Greek [Term?] (“apsides”) (plural form), from Ancient Greek ἁψίς (hapsís) (singular form)

definitionGroups.group: Of, or, pertaining to, the apsides

entries.meaning: (architecture) Of, pertaining to, or in the form of an apse or the apsides
(astronomy) Of or pertaining to an apsis or the apsides
